Reasoning: The paper focuses on the use of chatbots in software development to reduce friction points in collaboration. This topic falls under the intersection of computer science and social science, which is covered by the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of communication platforms and integrations, which are relevant to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. The paper also touches on software engineering practices and tools, which are covered by the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The use of chatbots and natural language processing also falls under the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the socio-technical aspects of collaborative work, which is relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
